ZH: 昨天我旷课去看电影了。
EN: I skipped class yesterday to watch a movie.

ZH: 他因为生病而旷课一周。
EN: He skipped a week of classes because he was sick.

ZH: 她总是旷课来迟。
EN: She always skips class and arrives late.

ZH: 我不得不旷课去参加家庭聚会。
EN: I had to skip class to attend a family gathering.

ZH: 学生们旷课的原因各不相同。
EN: The reasons why students skip class vary.

ZH: 他旷课是因为他懒散。
EN: He skips class because he is lazy.

ZH: 她旷课从来不告诉我。
EN: She never tells me when she skips class.

ZH: 警告：旷课会导致不及格。
EN: Warning: Skipping class can lead to failing grades.

ZH: 老师对旷课的学生不满意。
EN: The teacher is not pleased with students who skip class.

ZH: 我旷课的次数比较多。
EN: I skip class more often.

ZH: 他的旷课让班级的平均出勤率下降了。
EN: His skipping class caused the average attendance rate of the class to decrease.

ZH: 请你不要再旷课了。
EN: Please do not skip class anymore.

ZH: 我不能因为旷课而落后。
EN: I cannot fall behind because of skipping class.

ZH: 不要因为旷课而放弃学业。
EN: Don't give up on your studies because of skipping class.

ZH: 旷课会影响你的学习成绩。
EN: Skipping class will affect your academic performance.

ZH: 学校规定不能旷课。
EN: The school rules state that skipping class is not allowed.

ZH: 你为什么旷课？
EN: Why did you skip class?

ZH: 旷课对你的未来没有好处。
EN: Skipping class is not beneficial for your future.

ZH: 他没有任何理由旷课。
EN: He has no reason to skip class.

ZH: 我们应该珍惜每一节课，不要旷课。
EN: We should cherish every class and not skip any.
